INSERT INTO threads VALUES('019efa64-c524-72b1-9f2a-79d93acadf7e','C:\Users\Li\.codex\sessions\2026\06\25\rollout-2026-06-25T00-09-33-019efa64-c524-72b1-9f2a-79d93acadf7e.jsonl',1782317368,1782317393,'{"subagent":{"other":"guardian"}}','custom','E:\py_project\learn-claude-code',replace(replace('根据s05_todo_write的思想，我改造了code2.py，并且放到了s05的目录下。请根据s05下的code2.py代码，分析todo_write的思想并检查下面的输出是否符合：\012\012\012\012[15] user: \012# Files mentioned by the user:\012\012## s05 >> Review Python files under s05_todo_write/example and fix any style issue…: C:\Users\Li\.codex/attachments/61d575a5-a358-4146-a981-4fd9ebfd4e86/pasted-text.txt\012\012## My request for Codex:\012这是修改完系统提示词后的结果：\012\012\012[16] user: “教学版的 nag reminder（3 轮未更新就注入提醒）是教学机制。CC 源码中没有固定的"3 轮"逻辑，更接近的是 TodoWriteTool.ts:72-107 中当 3 个以上 todo 全部完成但没有 verification 项时，追加 verification nudge。”\012这个具体是如何实现的？\012\012\012[17] user: \012# Files mentioned by the user:\012\012## s06 >> Use a subtask to find what testing framework this project uses [HOOK] Us…: C:\Users\Li\.codex/attachments/2b5bbb5b-a16e-40d0-a157-1a9f544291aa/pasted-text.txt\012\012## My request for Codex:\012根据s06_subagent的教学内容，我修改了code2的内容放到了s06中，并且测试结果如下。请检查是否符合教学的内容？\012\012\012[18] user: 在代码层面，spawn_subagent和agent_loop的代码高度相似，请帮我解读一下，并进行对比。\012\012\012[19] user: Another language model started to solve this problem and produced a summary of its thinking process. You also have access to the state of the tools that were used by that language model. Use this to build on the work that has already been done and avoid duplicating work. Here is the summary produced by the other language model, use the information in this summary to assist with your own analysis:\012# Context Handoff Summary\012\012## Current State\012\012The user is building teaching examples (`code2.py` variants) of an agent harness, following the course at `E:\py_project\learn-claude-code`. Each chapter adds one mechanism on top of the previous. We are currently at **s06 (Subagent)**.\012\012## What Was Done This Conversation\012\012### s03 Permission — bugfix\012- Fixed: user approves outside-workspace write, but `safe_path()` still rejects it\012- Added `allow_outside_workspace` kwarg to `safe_path()`, `run_read()`, `run_write()`, `run_edit()`\012- `call_tool()` added as execution wrapper, passes approval to handlers\012\012### s04 Hooks — major rework of `code2.py`\012- Added `HookResult` dataclass with: `message`, `blockingError`, `outcome`, `preventContinuation`, `stopReason`, `permissionBehavior`, `updatedInput`, `additionalContext`, `updatedMCPToolOutput`\012- Added `normalize_hook_result()`, `merge_hook_result()`, `should_stop_hooks()`\012- `trigger_hooks()` now aggregates structured results, stops on deny/blocking\012- Hook order: `log_hook` before `permission_hook`\012- `call_tool()` now reads `permissionBehavior == "allow"` to decide `allow_outside_workspace`\012- Added `post_log_hook` so PostToolUse always prints (not just on >100k output)\012- Added `print_tool_output()` helper with `[TOOL OUTPUT]` tag\012- Fixed `run_shell()`: removed hardcoded `executable="cmd.exe"`, uses `COMSPEC` or system default\012- Chinese comments added to key sections (some got corrupted from bash encoding on first pass, then corrected via Python direct file write)\012\012### s05 TodoWrite — analysis\012- User''s `code2.py` had the mechanism working (tool, handler, counter, reminder)\012- First test: agent explored first, then planned — not ideal\012- Second test after SYSTEM prompt fix: `todo_write` was first tool call, plan → execute → complete, behavior improved significantly\012- Explained: CC''s verification nudge checks todo content (all completed but no verification step) vs teaching version''s round-count nag\012\012### s06 Subagent — analysis + detailed comparison\012- `spawn_subagent()` creates fresh `messages[]`, uses `SUB_TOOLS` (= no `task`/`todo_write`), `SUB_SYSTEM`, 30-turn safety limit\012- Returns only `extract_text()` summary; intermediate messages discarded\012- Subagent tool calls go through hooks (same `trigger_hooks` as parent)\012- **Key structural inconsistency found**: subagent calls `SUB_HANDLERS.get(...)(**input)` directly, not `call_tool()`. So `permissionBehavior="allow"` doesn''t feed into `allow_outside_workspace` for subagent file tools. Hook runs, but the result doesn''t fully propagate.\012- Provided a detailed 12-item comparison table between `agent_loop()` and `spawn_subagent()`\012- User''s test output for s06 was strong: parent called `task`, subagent did independent investigation, parent only received summary (`Stop: session used 1 tool calls`)\012\012## Key Architectural Patterns in the code2.py Variants\012\012- `SYSTEM` prompt guides behavior; `SUB_SYSTEM` for subagents (no delegate)\012- `TOOLS` vs `SUB_TOOLS`: sub-tools have no `task` or `todo_write`\012- `call_tool()` is the unified execution wrapper for parent; subagent bypasses it\012- Hooks (`HOOKS` dict, `register_hook`, `trigger_hooks`) are shared between parent and subagent (singleton)\012- `WORKDIR = Path.cwd().resolve()` — currently set to each chapter subdirectory, not the project root\012\012## Known Issues / Next Steps\012\0121. **Subagent execution bypasses `call_tool()`**: `spawn_subagent()` directly calls `SUB_HANDLERS.get(...)(**input)`. This means `permissionBehavior="allow"` from hooks is not consumed by the execution layer. Two options: extract `call_tool()` to accept a handler map parameter, or add a `call_sub_tool()`.\012\0122. **WORKDIR is chapter-specific**: e.g., `s06_subagent/` for s06. This means operations on the repo root (`tests/`, `requirements.txt`) trigger outside-workspace paths or require absolute paths via shell. May want to set `WORKDIR` to the repo root, or accept this as a teaching simplification.\012\0123. **SYSTEM string cut off**: in s06 code2.py line ~35: `"All destructive operations require "` — the last word `"user approval."` appears to be missing from the closing paren. Confirmed by reading the file.\012\0124. **Chinese comments have encoding issues**: when added via bash heredoc + `apply_patch`, Chinese characters were corrupted (displayed as `\ufffd` in some terminals). The actual file bytes are correct UTF-8, but the rendering may look wrong in PowerShell `cat`.\012\0125. **Next chapter (s07 Skill Loading)**: not yet started. The sequence would be loading external knowledge/skills on demand.\012\012## User Preferences\012\012- Works in `code2.py` files (teaching variants of `code.py`)\012- Uses PowerShell terminal, sometimes Python direct file writes for Chinese text\012- Prefers structured explanations with comparisons, tables, and code references\012- Interested in both "does it work" and "does it match the teaching goals"\012- Running model: `qwen3.7-plus` via DashScope (Anthropic-compatible API)\012\012[20] user: 检查一下s07中code2.py的代码，为什么我的工作路径不是项目根目录，而是当前的s07文件路径。并且导致我测试skill加载时出现下面的情况：\012\r\012s07 >> What skills are available?\r\012[HOOK] UserPromptSubmit: working in E:\py_project\learn-claude-code\s07_skill_loading\r\012[HOOK] Stop: session used 0 tool calls\r\012Based on the system information provided, there are currently **no skills available** in your workspace. The status shows "(no skills found)".\r\012\r\012This means there are no skill files (typically `.skill.md` or similar) in the `E:\py_project\learn-claude-code\s07_skill_loading` directory that can be loaded.\r\012\r\012If you''d like to:\r\012- Create new skills for this project\r\012- Check if there are any skill files in subdirectories\r\012- Learn about how skills work in Claude Code\r\012\r\012Let me know and I can help you with that!\012\012[48] user: 先分析一下s08的上下文压缩技术。\012\012\012[81] user: 把这四层压缩按照执行顺序具体介绍一下。包括他们之间的连接关系，触发条件等\012\012\012[83] user: messages条数和对话次数有什么区别？\012\012\012[85] user: 再检查一下code2.py的代码，能否符合基本的压缩处理。\012\012[109] user: 现在对s09_memory进行分析，并且以更加方便理解的方式讲出来帮助我学习其代码和思想。\012\012\012[127] user: 我在阅读代码的过程中，发现s09的code.py中少了关于skill的内容\012\012\012[129] user: 我希望两者并