tions and event writes should occur in the same SQLite transaction where possible.\012\012### JobManager\012\012Add `braincode/jobs/manager.py` as a thin durable service over SQLiteJobStore:\012\012- create/claim/heartbeat/complete/fail/cancel\012- update progress\012- poll durable terminal events\012- recover expired jobs\012- default project DB path: `.braincode/runtime.db`\012\012Do not add asyncio loops or Cron here.\012\012### TaskManager compatibility\012\012Change constructor to accept optional JobManager:\012\012```python\012TaskManager(job_manager: JobManager | None = None, ...)\012```\012\012Important compatibility decision:\012\012- `TaskManager()` with no manager must preserve existing in-memory behavior and tests.\012- Actual TUI/CLI runtime should explicitly inject JobManager.\012\012When durable:\012\012- `launch()` creates AGENT Job with same task ID as BackgroundTask.\012- Persist team name and `agent.work_dir` as `worktree_path`.\012- `_run_background()` claims the Job before running.\012- Pass `event_callback` to `run_to_completion()` and persist tool count/tokens/last activity.\012- Run periodic heartbeat during execution.\012- complete/fail/cancel both runtime asyncio task and durable Job.\012- `poll_completed()` should combine current in-memory queue and durable terminal events, avoiding duplicates.\012- BackgroundTask may need `agent: Agent | None` for recovered notifications; guard callers such as `app.py` before accessing `task.agent.agent_id`.\012\012Recovery:\012\012- Expired running Agent Jobs can be requeued by store.\012- If the worktree path no longer exists, mark clearly failed.\012- Since Phase 2 does not yet serialize/reconstruct Agent instances, unrecoverable Agent jobs should receive an explicit terminal failure rather than silently remain pending forever.\012\012### Runtime wiring\012\012TUI:\012\012- In `BraincodeApp`, create `.braincode/runtime.db`, SQLiteJobStore, JobManager, and inject into TaskManager.\012- Initialization ch