. Here is the summary produced by the other language model, use the information in this summary to assist with your own analysis:\012## Current task\012\012User requested Phase 5 of `改造方案.md`: structured `HookResult`, unified Hook integration, input/output/context modification, permission revalidation, and fixing the existing `Agent.run()` pre-tool Hook bypass.\012\012Per `改造方案.md`, implement only one Phase per turn. Do not start Phase 6.\012\012## Repository state\012\012- Workspace: `E:\py_project\Braincode`\012- Branch: `main`\012- Last pushed commit: `097c21e feat: add durable jobs and unified llm recovery`\012- Phase 4 and current partial Phase 5 changes are uncommitted.\012- Previously pushed Phase 1–3.\012- Phase 4 was completed before starting Phase 5:\012  - schema v3 schedules\012  - Cron parser/Scheduler\012  - background Bash and prompt runners\012  - Job/Cron tools and `/jobs`, `/cron`\012  - TUI/CLI/Remote wiring\012- Phase 4 validation before Phase 5:\012  - `624 passed, 2 skipped, 1 deselected`\012  - deselected test: `tests/test_hooks.py::TestAgentHookIntegration::test_pre_tool_use_reject_skips_tool`\012\012## Phase 5 decisions\012\012Structured result shape:\012\012```python\012@dataclass\012class HookResult:\012    outcome: str = "continue"\012    message: str = ""\012    reject_reason: str = ""\012    prevent_continuation: bool = False\012    updated_args: dict[str, Any] | None = None\012    updated_output: str | None = None\012    additional_context: str = ""\012```\012\012Decisions:\012\012- New Hook config supports a top-level `result:` mapping.\012- command/http action output may also contain HookResult JSON.\012- Legacy `reject: true` maps to structured reject.\012- Multiple results merge sequentially:\012  - reject/cancel stops later synchronous side-effect Hooks\012  - `prevent_continuation` ORs\012  - `updated_args` shallow-merge in Hook order\012  - latest `updated_output` wins\012  - additional contexts concatenate\012- Async Hooks may only provide notification/message/additional context.\012- Async updated args/output/reject/prevent are rejected by loader.\012- Tool parameters modified by Hook must be passed through PermissionChecker again.\012- Additional context is queued in HookEngine and injected as a later system reminder.\012\012## Phase 5 code already modified\012\012### Hook models and loader\012\012Modified:\012\012- `braincode/hooks/events.py`\012  - added `USER_PROMPT_SUBMIT`\012  - added `STOP`\012- `braincode/hooks/models.py`\012  - added `HookResult`\012  - `Hook.configured_result`\012  - `HookContext.tool_output`\012  - `$TOOL_OUTPUT` expansion\012- `braincode/hooks/loader.py`\012  - parses `result:`\012  - validates outcome and async restrictions\012- `braincode/hooks/__init__.py`\012  - exports HookResult helpers\012\012### Hook engine\012\012`braincode/hooks/engine.py` was replaced.\012\012It now contains:\012\012- `merge_hook_results`\012- `parse_hook_result`\012- `HookEngine.run_hooks(...) -> HookResult`\012- async Hook handling\012- queued additional contexts\012- legacy `run_pre_tool_hooks()` compatibility\012\012Review this file before continuing. Existing tests expect `run_pre_tool_hooks()` to return `ToolRejectedError`; compatibility wrapper remains.\012\012### Agent partial integration\012\012Modified `braincode/agent.py`:\012\012- imported `HookResult`\012- added `_hook_prevent_continuation`\012- `_build_hook_context()` includes `tool_output`\012- added:\012  - `_inject_hook_contexts()`\012  - `_apply_pre_tool_hooks()`\012  - `_apply_post_tool_hooks()`\012- partially integrated pre/post hooks into:\012  - `_execute_single_tool_direct()`\012  - `_execute_tool()`\012  - `_execute_tool_noninteractive()`\012\012No tests have been run after these partial Agent edits.\012\012## Critical incomplete/broken area\012\012The current `braincode/agent.py` permission logic was patched incrementally and must be reviewed carefully before testing.\012\012Inspect these sections:\012\012```powershell\012Get-Content braincode/agent.py | Select-Object -Skip 820 -First 240\012Get-Content braincode/agent.py | Select-Object -Skip 1320 -First 140\012```\012\012Likely issues:\012\0121. `_execute_tool()` permission-request block is overly convoluted.\0122. A patch intended for `_execute_tool_noninteractive()` may have inserted a `decision.effect == "deny"` check into the first matching block instead.\0123. Ensure updated arguments are:\012   - merged before validation/execution\012   - passed to PermissionChecker\012   - passed to Pydantic model validation\012   - used in recovery snapshots/post Hooks\0124. Ensure PermissionChecker remains final:\012   - updated allow → ask should prompt in interactive path\012   - updated allow → deny must reject\012   - noninteractive ask must fail, except existing BYPASS semantics\0125. Ensure pre/post Hooks run exactly once on each path.\012\012Recommended next step: refactor these three methods around shared helpers instead of more incremental branching.\012\012## Remaining Phase 5 work\012\012### 1. Finish unified tool lifecycle\012\012All three paths must implement:\012\012```text\012tool exists/enabled\012→ pre_tool_use Hook\012→ apply updated_args\012→ PermissionChecker on final args\012→ permission_request Hook if needed\012→ parameter validation\012→ execute\012→ recovery snapshot\012→ post_tool_use Hook\012→ apply updated_output\012→ honor prevent_continuation\012```\012\012Paths:\012\012- `_execute_single_tool_direct()`\012- `_execute_tool()`\012- `_execute_tool_noninteractive()`\012\012The original failing Hook test must pass afterward.\012\012### 2. Integrate structured lifecycle events\012\012Needed events:\012\012- `user_prompt_submit`\012- `session_start/session_end`\012- `turn_start/turn_end`\012- `pre_send/post_receive`\012- `pre_tool_use/post_tool_use`\012- `permission_request`\012- `stop`\012\012For lifecycle results:\012\012- inject `additional_context`\012- `post_receive.updated_output` should replac