ired-field questions, also use `mcp__openaiDeveloperDocs__get_openapi_spec` when available. Official-domain web search is fallback after those tools are unavailable or unhelpful. Broad Codex questions use the manual helper before Docs MCP. This skill also owns model selection, API model migration, and prompt-upgrade guidance.\015\012\015\012## API Key Setup\015\012\015\012For requests to build, run, configure, debug, or implement an API-backed app, script, CLI, generator, or tool, use `openai-platform-api-key` first when available. After that credential gate is resolved, return here for current docs as needed.\015\012\015\012Use this skill directly for docs-only questions, citations, model/API guidance, conceptual explanations, and examples that do not require building or running an API-backed artifact.\015\012\015\012## Workflow Configuration\015\012\015\012### Source Priority\015\012\015\012- For Codex self-knowledge, use the Codex source route below; it owns when to use the manual helper, Docs MCP, or bounded uncertainty.\015\012- For non-Codex OpenAI docs questions, use `mcp__openaiDeveloperDocs__search_openai_docs` to find the most relevant doc pages.\015\012- For non-Codex OpenAI docs questions, fetch th<truncated omitted_approx_tokens="3742" />est/latest/current model" questions.\015\012- `scripts/fetch-codex-manual.mjs` -> current Codex manual fetch, verification, local temp cache, and outline generation.\015\012- `https://developers.openai.com/codex/codex-manual.md` -> current Codex self-knowledge synthesis, including setup, customization, skills, plugins, MCP, hooks, `AGENTS.md`, automations, and surface behavior; normally access it through the helper path and targeted file reads when temp caching is available.\015\012- `references/latest-model.md` -> bundled fallback for model-selection and "best/latest/current model" questions.\015\012- `references/upgrade-guide.md` -> bundled fallback for model upgrade and upgrade-planning requests.\015\012- `references/prompting-guide.md` -> bundled fallback for prompt rewrites and prompt-behavior upgrades.\015\012\015\012## Quality rules\015\012\015\012- Treat OpenAI docs as the source of truth; avoid speculation.\015\012- For Codex self-knowledge, follow the source route above instead of relying on remembered behavior.\015\012- Keep migration changes narrow and behavior-preserving.\015\012- Prefer prompt-only upgrades when possible.\015\012- Avoid inventing pricing, availability, parameters, API changes, or breaking changes.\015\012- Keep quotes short and within policy limits; prefer paraphrase with citations.\015\012- If multiple pages differ, call out the difference and cite both.\015\012- If official docs and verified callable current-session behavior disagree, state the conflict before making broad claims or edits.\015\012- If docs do not cover the user鈥檚 need, say so and offer next steps.\015\012\015\012## Tooling notes\015\012\015\012- Use MCP doc tools before web search for OpenAI-related markdown docs. The Codex manual flow is the exception: follow the Codex self-knowledge source procedure for broad Codex synthesis.\015\012- If the MCP server is installed but returns no meaningful results, then use web search as a fallback.\015\012- When falling back to web search, restrict to official OpenAI domains (developers.openai.com, platform.openai.com) and cite sources.\015\012\015\012\012\012[32] assistant: `openai-docs` 流程要求先核对当前 Codex 手册中 MCP、skill 与 `AGENTS.md` 的职责边界；我会同时做本机状态检查。检查配置时会隐藏 API Key，不会把密钥输出到对话。\012\012[33] tool exec call: const results = await Promise.all([\012  tools.exec_command({\012    cmd: "node ''C:\\Users\\Li\\.codex\\skills\\.system\\openai-docs\\scripts\\fetch-codex-manual.mjs''",\012    shell: "powershell",\012    login: false,\012    yield_time_ms: 30000,\012    max_output_tokens: 10000\012  }),\012  tools.exec_command({\012    cmd: "$config = ''C:\\Users\\Li\\.codex\\config.toml''; Write-Output ''CONTEXT7 CONFIG:''; if (Test-Path -LiteralPath $confi