from a curated list or a GitHub repo path. Use when a user asks to list installable skills, install a curated skill, or install a skill from another repo (including private repos).\015\012metadata:\015\012  short-description: Install curated skills from openai/skills or other repos\015\012---\015\012\015\012# Skill Installer\015\012\015\012Helps install skills. By default these are from https://github.com/openai/skills/tree/main/skills/.curated, but users can also provide other locations. Experimental skills live in https://github.com/openai/skills/tree/main/skills/.experimental and can be installed the same way.\015\012\015\012Use the helper scripts based on the task:\015\012- List skills when the user asks what is available, or if the user uses this skill without specifying what to do. Default listing is `.curated`, but you can pass `--path skills/.experimental` when they ask about experimental skills.\015\012- Install from the curated list when the user provides a skill name.\015\012- Install from another repo when the user provides a GitHub repo/path (including private repos).\015\012\015\012Install skills with the helper scripts.\015\012\015\012## Communication\015\012\015\012When listing skills, output approximately as follows, depending on the context of the user''s request. If they ask about experimental skills, list from `.experimental` instead of `.curated` and label the source accordingly:\015\012"""\015\012Skills from {repo}:\015\0121. skill-1\015\0122. skill-2 (already installed)\015\0123. ...\015\012Which ones would you like installed?\015\012"""\015\012\015\012After installing a skill, tell the user it will be available on their next turn.\015\012\015\012## Scripts\015\012\015\012All of these scripts use network, so when running in the sandbox, request escalation when running them.\015\012\015\012- `scripts/list-skills.py` (prints skills list with installed annotations)\015\012- `scripts/list-skills.py --format json`\015\012- Example (experimental list): `scripts/list-skills.py --path skills/.experimental`\015\012- `scripts/install-skill-from-github.py --repo <owner>/<repo> --path <path/to/skill> [<path/to/skill> ...]`\015\012- `scripts/install-skill-from-github.py --url https://github.com/<owner>/<repo>/tree/<ref>/<path>`\015\012- Example (experimental skill): `scripts/install-skill-from-github.py --repo openai/skills --path skills/.experimental/<skill-name>`\015\012\015\012## Behavior and Options\015\012\015\012- Defaults to direct download for public GitHub repos.\015\012- If download fails with auth/permission errors, falls back to git sparse checkout.\015\012- Aborts if the destination skill directory already exists.\015\012- Installs into `$CODEX_HOME/skills/<skill-name>` (defaults to `~/.codex/skills`).\015\012- Multiple `--path` values install multiple skills in one run, each named from the path basename unless `--name` is supplied.\015\012- Options: `--ref <ref>` (default `main`), `--dest <path>`, `--method auto|download|git`.\015\012\015\012## Notes\015\012\015\012- Curated listing is fetched from `https://github.com/openai/skills/tree/main/skills/.curated` via the GitHub API. If it is unavailable, explain the error and exit.\015\012- Private GitHub repos can be accessed via existing git credentials or optional `GITHUB_TOKEN`/`GH_TOKEN` for download.\015\012- Git fallback tries HTTPS first, then SSH.\015\012- The skills at https://github.com/openai/skills/tree/main/skills/.system are preinstalled, so no need to help users install those. If they ask, just explain this. If they insist, you can download and overwrite.\015\012- Installed annotations come from `$CODEX_HOME/skills`.\015\012\015\012\012\012[5] assistant: 我已读完本机的 skill 管理说明。接下来会同时检查技能目录名、`SKILL.md` 元数据以及可能的插件注册项；删除前先列出精确命中路径。\012\012[6] tool exec call: const r = await tools.exec_command({\012  cmd: "$roots = @(''C:\\Users\\Li\\.codex\\skills'',''C:\\Users\\Li\\.agents\\skills'',''C:\\Users\\Li\\.codex\\plugins''); foreach ($root in $roots) { i