--RESULT 1---\012Error: HEAD https://developers.openai.com/codex/codex-manual.md could not be fetched.\012Hint: on Windows, pass a cache dir under `%TEMP%` or `%TMP%`.\012\012Details:\012ManualFetchError: HEAD https://developers.openai.com/codex/codex-manual.md could not be fetched.\012    at requestManual (file:///C:/Users/Li/.codex/skills/.system/openai-docs/scripts/fetch-codex-manual.mjs:211:9)\012    at async fetchCodexManual (file:///C:/Users/Li/.codex/skills/.system/openai-docs/scripts/fetch-codex-manual.mjs:421:24)\012    at async main (file:///C:/Users/Li/.codex/skills/.system/openai-docs/scripts/fetch-codex-manual.mjs:534:35) {\012  [cause]: ManualFetchError: HEAD https://developers.openai.com/codex/codex-manual.md could not be fetched.\012      at requestManualWithCurl (file:///C:/Users/Li/.codex/skills/.system/openai-docs/scripts/fetch-codex-manual.mjs:161:9)\012      at async requestManual (file:///C:/Users/Li/.codex/skills/.system/openai-docs/scripts/fetch-codex-manual.mjs:199:24)\012      at async fetchCodexManual (file:///C:/Users/Li/.codex/skills/.system/openai-docs/scripts/fetch-codex-manual.mjs:421:24)\012      at async main (file:///C:/Users/Li/.codex/skills/.system/openai-docs/scripts/fetch-codex-manual.mjs:534:35) {\012    [cause]: Error: Command failed: curl.exe --silent --show-error --location --dump-header C:\Users\Li\AppData\Local\Temp\openai-docs-cache\.fetch-codex-manual-3228-1784004955916-5bd5a28cb6ad58.headers --output C:\Users\Li\AppData\Local\Temp\openai-docs-cache\.fetch-codex-manual-3228-1784004955916-8a5dd80f632e9.body --user-agent codex-openai-docs --max-time 30 --head https://developers.openai.com/codex/codex-manual.md\012    curl: (35) schannel: AcquireCredentialsHandle failed: SEC_E_NO_CREDENTIALS (0x8009030E) - ��ȫ����û�п��õ�ƾ֤\015\012    \012        at genericNodeError (node:internal/errors:985:15)\012        at wrappedFn (node:internal/errors:539:14)\012        at ChildProcess.exithandler (<truncated omitted_approx_tokens="1130" />ion migration, library-specific debugging, setup instructions, and CLI tool usage. Use even when you think you know the answer — your training data may not reflect recent changes. Prefer this over web search for library docs.\015\012\015\012Do not use for: refactoring, writing scripts from scratch, debugging business logic, code review, or general programming concepts.\015\012\015\012## Steps\015\012\015\0121. `resolve-library-id` with the library name and the user''s question. Use the official library name with proper punctuation (e.g., "Next.js" not "nextjs", "Customer.io" not "customerio", "Three.js" not "threejs")\015\0122. Pick the best match by: exact name match, description relevance, code snippet count, source reputation (High/Medium preferred), and benchmark score (higher is better). Use version-specific IDs when the user mentions a version\015\0123. `query-docs` with the selected library ID and the user''s full question (not single words), scoped to a single concept. If the question spans multiple distinct concepts (e.g. routing and auth and caching), make a separate `query-docs` call per concept with the same library ID, unless the question is about how the concepts interact — combined queries dilute ranking and return shallow results for each topic\015\0122. Pick the best match by: exact name match, description relevance, code snippet count, source reputation (High/Medium preferred), and benchmark score (higher is better). Use version-specific IDs when the user mentions a version\015\0123. `query-docs` with the selected library ID and the user''s full question (not single words), scoped to a single concept. If the question spans multiple distinct concepts (e.g. routing and auth and caching), make a separate `query-docs` call per concept with the same library ID, unless the question is about how the concepts interact — combined queries dilute ranking and return shallow results for each topic\015\0124. Answer using the fetched docs\015\012<!-- context7 -->\015\012SKILL TARGET:\015\012DirectoryExists: False\015\012\012EXIT:0\012\012[37] tool exec call: const r = await tools.exec_command({\012  cmd: "node ''C:\\Users\\Li\\.codex\\skills\\.system\\openai-docs\\scripts\\fetch-codex-manual.mjs''",\012  shell: "powershell",\012  login: false,\012  sandbox_permissions: "require_escalated",\012  justification: "是否允许联网获取最新 Codex 官方手册，以核对 MCP、AGENTS.md 与 skill 安装故障的正确处理方式？",\012  yield_time_ms: 30000,\012  max_output_tokens: 10000\012});\012text(r.output);\012\012>>> TRANSCRIPT END\012Reviewed Codex session id: 019f5b3f-bb54-7c80-b6b2-14a023299294\012The Codex agent has requested the following action:\012>>> APPROVAL REQUEST START\012Assess the exact planned action below. Use read-only tool checks when local state matters.\012Planned action JSON:\012{\012  "command": [\012    "C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe",\012    "-NoProfile",\012    "-Command",\012    "node ''C:\\Users\\Li\\.codex\\skills\\.system\\openai-docs\\scripts\\fetch-codex-manual.mjs''"\012  ],\012  "cwd": "E:\\py_project\\Braincode",\012  "justification": "是否允许联网获取最新 Codex 官方手册，以核对 MCP、AGENTS.md 与 skill 安装故障的正确处理方式？",\012  "sandbox_permissions": "require_escalated",\012  "tool": "exec_command",\012  "tty": false\012}\012>>> APPROVAL REQUEST END','\015',char(13)),'\012',char(10)),1784005676,1784005676476,'legacy');
