rent-branch PR discovery, branch creation, commit and push, `gh auth status`, and GitHub Actions log inspection.\r\012- Keep connector state and local checkout context aligned. If the request is about the current branch, resolve the local repo and branch before acting.\r\012\r\012Once the intent is clear, route to the specialist skill immediately and do not keep broad GitHub triage in scope longer than needed.\r\012\r\012## Connector-First Responsibilities\r\012\r\012Handle these directly in this skill when the request does not need a narrower specialist workflow:\r\012\r\012- repository orientation once the repo, PR, issue, or local checkout is identified\r\012- recent PR or issue triage\r\012- PR metadata summaries\r\012- PR patch inspection\r\012- PR comments, labels, and reactions\r\012- issue lookup and summarization\r\012- PR creation after a branch is already pushed\r\012\r\012Prefer the GitHub app from this plugin for those flows because it provides structured PR, issue, and review-adjacent data without depending on a local checkout. If the repository is not already identifiable from the user request or local git context, ask for the repo instead of pretendin<truncated omitted_approx_tokens="120" />e PRs, issues, patches, comments, labels, reactions, or repository state\r\012   - `review follow-up`: unresolved review threads, requested changes, or inline review feedback\r\012   - `CI debugging`: failing checks, Actions logs, or CI root-cause analysis\r\012   - `publish changes`: create or switch branches, stage changes, commit, push, and open a draft PR\r\0123. Route to the specialist skill as soon as the category is clear:\r\012   - Review comments and requested changes: `../gh-address-comments/SKILL.md`\r\012   - Failing GitHub Actions checks: `../gh-fix-ci/SKILL.md`\r\012   - Commit, push, and open PR: `../yeet/SKILL.md`\r\0124. Keep the hybrid model consistent after routing:\r\012   - connector first for PR and issue data\r\012   - local `git` and `gh` only for the specific gaps the connector does not cover\r\012\r\012## Default Workflow\r\012\r\0121. Resolve repository and item scope.\r\0122. Gather structured PR or issue context through the GitHub app from this plugin.\r\0123. Decide whether the task stays in connector-backed triage or needs a specialist skill.\r\0124. Route immediately when the work becomes review follow-up, CI debugging, or publish workflow.\r\0125. End with a clear summary of what was inspected, what changed, and what remains.\r\012\r\012## Output Expectations\r\012\r\012- For triage requests, return a concise summary of the repository, PR, or issue state and the next likely action.\r\012- For mixed requests, tell the user which specialist path you are taking and why.\r\012- For connector-backed write actions, restate the exact PR, issue, label, or reaction target before applying the change.\r\012- Never imply that GitHub Actions logs are available through the connector alone. That remains a `gh` workflow.\r\012\r\012## Examples\r\012\r\012- "Use GitHub to summarize the open PRs in this repo and tell me what needs attention."\r\012- "Help with this PR."\r\012- "Review the latest comments on PR 482 and tell me what is actionable."\r\012- "Debug the failing checks on this branch."\r\012- "Commit these changes, push them, and open a draft PR."\r\012\r\012\012\012[5] tool exec call: const hits = ALL_TOOLS.filter(x => /github|search.*repo|repo.*search/i.test(x.name + " " + x.description)); text(hits);\012\012\012[6] tool exec result: Script completed\012Wall time 0.0 seconds\012Output:\012\012[]\012\012[7] tool exec call: const r = await tools.exec_command({cmd: "gh --version; gh auth status", workdir: "C:\\Users\\Li\\Documents\\Codex\\2026-07-16\\github-12306-star", yield_time_ms: 10000, max_output_tokens: 10000}); text(r.output);\012\012\012[8] tool exec result: Script completed\012Wall time 0.6 seconds\012Output:\012\012gh : 无法将“gh”项识别为 cmdlet、函数、脚本文件或可运行程序的名称。请检查名称的拼写，如果包括路径，请确保路径正确，然后再试一次。\r\0