n connector-backed triage or needs a specialist skill.\r\0124. Route immediately when the work becomes review follow-up, CI debugging, or publish workflow.\r\0125. End with a clear summary of what was inspected, what changed, and what remains.\r\012\r\012## Output Expectations\r\012\r\012- For triage requests, return a concise summary of the repository, PR, or issue state and the next likely action.\r\012- For mixed requests, tell the user which specialist path you are taking and why.\r\012- For connector-backed write actions, restate the exact PR, issue, label, or reaction target before applying the change.\r\012- Never imply that GitHub Actions logs are available through the connector alone. That remains a `gh` workflow.\r\012\r\012## Examples\r\012\r\012- "Use GitHub to summarize the open PRs in this repo and tell me what needs attention."\r\012- "Help with this PR."\r\012- "Review the latest comments on PR 482 and tell me what is actionable."\r\012- "Debug the failing checks on this branch."\r\012- "Commit these changes, push them, and open a draft PR."\r\012\r\012\012\012[5] tool exec call: const hits = ALL_TOOLS.filter(x => /github|search.*repo|repo.*search/i.test(x.name + " " + x.description)); text(hits);\012\012\012[6] tool exec result: Script completed\012Wall time 0.0 seconds\012Output:\012\012[]\012\012[7] tool exec call: const r = await tools.exec_command({cmd: "gh --version; gh auth status", workdir: "C:\\Users\\Li\\Documents\\Codex\\2026-07-16\\github-12306-star", yield_time_ms: 10000, max_output_tokens: 10000}); text(r.output);\012\012\012[8] tool exec result: Script completed\012Wall time 0.6 seconds\012Output:\012\012gh : 无法将“gh”项识别为 cmdlet、函数、脚本文件或可运行程序的名称。请检查名称的拼写，如果包括路径，请确保路径正确，然后再试一次。\r\012所在位置 行:2 字符: 1\r\012+ gh --version; gh auth status\r\012+ ~~\r\012    + CategoryInfo          : ObjectNotFound: (gh:String) [], CommandNotFoundException\r\012    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : CommandNotFoundException\r\012 \r\012gh : 无法将“gh”项识别为 cmdlet、函数、脚本文件或可运